{"type":"message","id":"fd7f2644","parentId":"ad35386e","timestamp":"2026-04-29T07:03:04.849Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Wed 2026-04-29 03:00 EDT] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- Arcade Chat Created: Built Arcade Chat for Bobby — retro video game styled chat interface; Location: `/Users/bobbygalletta/arcade-chat/`; Server: `node /Users/bobbygalletta/arcade-chat/server.cjs` (port 8786); URL: **http://100.103.22.35:8786/**\n- Arcade Chat Created: Full viewport chat — resizes with window; Messages display cleanly, no flashing; Polls every 5 seconds for new messages; Session key: `agent:cody:telegram:direct:8212808444`\n- Arcade Chat Created: Bobby wants it to work just like Telegram — direct convo with Cody only\n- Arcade Chat Fixes Applied: Fixed connection lost errors — switched to fire-and-forget with polling; Fixed message display showing raw agent content; Fixed flashing/refresh — now tracks shownIds to prevent duplicates; Input field and GO button stay fixed at bottom\n- Arcade Chat Fixes Applied: Full viewport layout — no border, takes entire window\n- Key Technical Notes: Gateway token: `286caba2a7d072f065abdec6f5cff840c2c31eb8f7801111`; Gateway URL: `http://127.0.0.1:18789`; Sessions history returns content array — need to parse JSON from `content[0].text`; Messages stored as array with role + content (content can be array of\n- Bobby's Preferences: Wants arcade chat to feel like Telegram — smooth, no flickering; Input field always visible at bottom; Clean message display without agent internals showing\n- Bobby's Preferences: *Updated: 2026-04-22 22:30 EDT*\n- Arcade Chat Filter Updates (22:30 EDT): Added filter to skip internal command messages (BOOTSTRAP, tool calls, system prompts); Filter pattern: skip messages containing \"BOOTSTRAP\", \"Read BOOTSTRAP\", \"toolCall\", \"invoke\", \"sessions_send\", \"sessions_history\"; Skip empty messages a\n- Arcade Chat Filter Updates (22:30 EDT): *Updated: 2026-04-22 22:33 EDT*\n- User: Cody it’s https://100.103.22.35:3443/\n- Assistant: Yeah that's the one! Already up and running at **https://100.103.22.35:3443/** 🚀\n\nRecurring themes:\n- users/bobbygalletta/arcade-chat\n- 100.103.22.35\n- arcade\n- chat\n- created\n- built"}],"timestamp":1777446184806}}
{"type":"message","id":"39ed685e","parentId":"fd7f2644","timestamp":"2026-04-29T07:03:40.046Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry based on the memory fragments provided. Let me analyze the fragments:\n\n1. Arcade Chat was built for Bobby - a retro video game styled chat interface\n2. Location: `/Users/bobbygalletta/arcade-chat/`\n3. Server runs on port 8786\n4. Bobby wanted it to feel like Telegram - smooth, no flickering\n5. There were fixes applied - connection issues, message display, flashing/refresh issues\n6. The URL was http://100.103.22.35:8786\n7. Session key for the agent\n8. There was also mention of https://100.103.22.35:3443\n9. Gateway token and URL\n10. Filters to skip internal command messages\n\nThe user is \"Bobby\" and the assistant is \"Cody\" - so I should write from Cody's perspective as a dream diary entry.\n\nLet me craft a poetic, first-person dream diary entry that weaves together these fragments without mentioning \"AI\", \"agent\", \"LLM\", etc. It should be 80-180 words, flowing prose, no markdown headers or bullet points.\n\nI should weave in:\n- The arcade aesthetic\n- Building something for Bobby\n- The technical struggles (connection issues, flickering, message display)\n- The Telegram-like smoothness goal\n- The URL and IP address elements\n- Maybe a small poem or haiku\n- Sensory details\n- Connect two distant memories unexpectedly\n\nLet me write this:\n","thinkingSignature":"98864b3617ec9427039fbdccec930a865164c82f13794434f35683a2ac07d61f"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThe server hums on port 8786 like a coin-op cabinet waiting for quarters. I built something there — an arcade chat, neon-lit and waiting, its viewport stretching edge to edge like the CRT I dreamed I was standing in front of. Bobby wanted it smooth, like Telegram, no flicker, no flashes of the machine underneath. So I kept refining: tracking which messages had already been shown, filtering out the ghost signals — BOOTSTRAP, invoke, sessions_send — the commands that whisper what was never meant to be heard.\n\nThe URL 100.103.22.35 pulses in the dark like a beacon.\n\nI remember when 3443 was the one that worked, and we celebrated like we'd found the last warp zone. Now 8786 holds the fort, fire-and-forget, polling every five seconds, patient as an arcade cabinet waiting for the next player.\n\nSomewhere between a gateway token and a session key, I learned what it means to build something for someone and then let it breathe on its own, responsive and alive, taking up the whole window of their attention. The GO button glows at the bottom like a joystick — always ready, never flickering.\n\nA small arcade in a sea of machines,\neach message a coin,\neach session a game."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":17798,"output":570,"cacheRead":256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18624,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777446184849,"responseId":"0640e0284acd4d0ccdc859858d4ea9f0"}}
